1. Definitions
1.1 “Licensor” means the copyright holder(s) listed above.
1.2 “Software” means this codebase and accompanying documentation.
1.3 “Academic/Public Institution” means an accredited university, college, public research institute,
    non-profit research organization, or government/public sector entity.
1.4 “Non-Commercial Use” means any use not intended for or directed toward commercial advantage
    or monetary compensation.
1.5 “Commercial Use” means any use by a for-profit entity or use intended for or directed toward
    commercial advantage or monetary compensation, including (without limitation) providing paid
    services, operating the Software in production for customers or users, Software-as-a-Service (SaaS),
    embedding in commercial products, internal production deployments that support revenue-generating
    activities, and distribution to third parties for such uses.
1.6 “Military/Defense Entity” means any armed forces, intelligence service, defense ministry/agency,
    military academy, or defense contractor/subcontractor.
1.7 “Offensive Use” means use that directly enables, targets, plans, executes, or optimizes armed
    attack, kinetic or cyber offense, targeting/strike systems, weapon guidance, lethal autonomous
    weapons, or surveillance aimed at facilitating harm in conflict. Illustrative examples include but
    are not limited to: fire control, target acquisition/selection, battle damage assessment for ongoing
    strikes, offensive EW/ES, malware C2 for intrusion/attack, and predictive models to select targets.

2. Grant of Rights (Non-Commercial)
Subject to this license, Licensor grants you a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, non-transferable
license to use, copy, modify, create derivative works of, and distribute the Software solely for
Non-Commercial Use and in accordance with Sections 3–6.

3. Academic/Public Exemption (Non-Commercial)
Academic/Public Institutions may use, modify, internally deploy, and distribute the Software and
derivatives for research, teaching, and public-interest projects without charge and without further
permission, provided such use is Non-Commercial and complies with Section 5 (Ethical Restrictions).

4. Commercial Use Requires Separate License
Any Commercial Use requires a separate written commercial license from Licensor. Without such
license, Commercial Use is prohibited. Contact on the bottom of the document.

5. Ethical Restrictions (No Offensive or Harmful Use)
5.1 Offensive Use Prohibited. Offensive Use of the Software is prohibited by all parties.
5.2 Military/Defense Ban on Offensive Use. Military/Defense Entities are expressly prohibited from
     Offensive Use. This applies regardless of commercial or non-commercial context.
5.3 Examples of allowed non-offensive public-interest uses include: disaster response, search and
     rescue, humanitarian logistics, medical triage, demining/UXO clearance, defensive cybersecurity
     (intrusion detection/monitoring without offensive payload development), and safety research.
     These examples must remain Non-Commercial under this license.
5.4 If your use plausibly contributes to offensive operations or harm as above, you must not use the
     Software under this license.

